Package org.sbml.squeezer.math

Class org.sbml.squeezer.math.SBMLinterpreter extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: 3453063382705340995L

Serialized Fields

currentTime

double currentTime

currentReaction

org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction currentReaction
This field is necessary to also consider local parameters of the current reaction because it is not possible to access these parameters from the model. Hence we have to memorize an additional reference to the Reaction and thus to the list of these parameters.

valuesHash

java.util.HashMap<K,V> valuesHash
An array, which stores all computed initial values of the model. If this model does not contain initial assignments, the initial values will only be taken once from the information stored in the model. Otherwise they have to be computed again as soon as the parameter values of this model are changed, because the parameters may influence the return values of the initial assignments.

listOfContraintsViolations

java.util.List<E>[] listOfContraintsViolations
An array, which stores for each constraint the list of times, in which the constraint was violated during the simulation.

listOfEvents_delay

java.util.LinkedList<E>[] listOfEvents_delay
This array data structure stores at the position i a list of time (double values) at which the event with ID equals i must be executed. The value before last of the list ist the watcher. It can be POSITIVE_INFINITY if the trigger expession has the value trueor NaN if value of trigger expression is false

model

org.sbml.jsbml.Model model
The model to be simulated.

speciesIdIndex

java.util.Map<K,V> speciesIdIndex
This map data structure is necessary to save the index of every species within the model system since libSBML doesn't provide the index of a species for a given name. This, however, is necessary to work with an array containing the concentrations of the species.

swap

double[] swap
This array is to avoid to allocate memory repeatedly. It stores the values computed during the linear combination of velocities. These values are passed to the array Y afterwards.

v

double[] v
An array of the velocities of each reaction within the model system. Holding this globally saves many new memory allocations during simulation time.

Y

double[] Y
An array of the current concentration of each species within the model system.
